  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p>- Supervise and manage site activities to ensure timely project execution</p><p>- Coordinate with subcontractors, consultants, and clients</p><p>- Prepare site reports, inspection requests, and method statements</p><p>- Ensure compliance with safety, quality, and regulatory standards</p><p>- Monitor progress and handle site issues effectively</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>- Degree/Diploma in accounts or arts and science <br /></p><p>- Minimum 2–3 years of relevant experience in construction projects (fresh grads may apply)</p><p>- Good knowledge of structural and architectural drawings</p><p>- Familiar with local codes and site procedures</p><p>- Able to work independently and lead a team</p><p>- Strong problem-solving and communication skills</p><p>Working Hours: Monday to Saturday</p><p>Salary: $4200</p>",
